  <!-- Main Content -->
  <main class="flex-grow container max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 pt-16 pb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Welcome</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Welcome to <strong>jgwalsh.net</strong>. This site highlights my background in psychology, data analysis, and law enforcement readiness.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4">
      I have over three years of experience as a mental health specialist at
      <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/McLean_Hospital"
         target="_blank"
         rel="noopener noreferrer"
         class="text-blue-700 underline">McLean Hospital</a>,
      specifically within the
      <a href="https://www.mcleanhospital.org/treatment/mclean-franciscan-child-and-adolescent-inpatient-program"
         target="_blank"
         rel="noopener noreferrer"
         class="text-blue-700 underline">McLean-Franciscan</a>
      unit, a psychiatric hospital in Brighton, Massachusetts, affiliated with Harvard Medical School. My work involved
      clinical assessment, crisis intervention, and interdisciplinary collaboration within acute psychiatric settings.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4">
      My educational foundation in psychology—spanning undergraduate and graduate-level training—is enhanced by strong
      quantitative and analytical capabilities, particularly using SPSS, R, and Excel.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Returning home to Albany, New York, during the COVID-19 pandemic coincided with significant transformations in
      clinical psychology and the broader mental health system, most notably the rise of teletherapy. Observing these
      changes inspired me to reconsider my career direction and explore how my experience might align with alternative
      professional pathways. This period of reassessment has motivated my current pursuit of opportunities within
      federal or state law enforcement, aiming to address critical challenges facing local communities and the nation.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-4">Core Competencies</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-4">
      <li><strong>Behavioral Assessment and Crisis Intervention</strong></li>
      <li><strong>Interdisciplinary Collaboration and Communication</strong></li>
      <li><strong>Advanced Quantitative Analysis</strong> (SPSS, R, Excel)</li>
      <li><strong>Applied Psychological Principles</strong></li>
      <li><strong>Adaptability, Critical Thinking, and Analytical Problem-Solving</strong></li>
    </ul>
  </main>

